    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I'm Lon'qu, a swordsman from Regna Ferox. And...that's all there is to know about me.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "I hope to truly master the sword...but something might be throwing off my hand. Maybe if I...steadied myself around women, that would do the trick.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Before becoming a Shepherd, I was right hand to Basilio, West-Khan of Regna Ferox.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "If you are too busy, I can patrol in your stead.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "Would you care to spar? If you have no combat training, you could always throw rocks at me.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I was just sharpening my sword. If it won't work when I need it, then that will be the end of me.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I think you're the one I was sent here to find. You know <Friend Name>, yes? I'm here to deliver a hello. Now that I have, I will leave.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "This is only the start of what I can do.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "...Good.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "The path to mastering the sword is a lonely one.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Being granted power instead of slowly earning it...isn't so bad.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "You're here again. Why? What have I done to deserve this attention? I have no wealth, no power. Nothing but my skills as a swordsman. What? You value my presence? You find my help...reassuring? No one has ever said that to me before, but I am glad my presence gives you strength. Understood. I shall be your bodyguard, then. I will stay by your side for as long as you want me.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
